\begin_layout Subsection
Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The goal of this work is not to optimise benchmark performance,
 but to explore the design space of long-lived,
 inspectable agent systems.
 We treat the system as an engineering artefact and report its observed behaviour under deployment.
 The evidence is drawn from a single instance (
\begin_inset Formula $n=1$
\end_inset

) and is anecdotal;
 its role is illustrative,
 not conclusive.
\end_layout

