\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
Curator
\series default
 (
\family typewriter
narrative/curator.gleam
\family default
) assembles a virtual context window each cycle,
 following the Letta-style approach of treating the LLM's context as a managed resource rather than a passive conversation history.
 The context window is divided into priority-budgeted slots,
 each assigned a priority level from
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

1 (identity) through
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

10 (background).
 At assembly time,
 the Curator loads the agent's persona and character specification,
 queries the Librarian for active thread count,
 persistent fact count,
 and CBR case count,
 renders the sensorium XML (Section
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:sensorium"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

),
 retrieves relevant CBR cases organised by category,
 and populates the session preamble template using 
\family typewriter
{{slot}}
\family default
 substitution with 
\family typewriter
[OMIT IF]
\family default
 conditional rules.
 When total content exceeds the configurable character budget (
\family typewriter
preamble_budget_chars
\family default
,
 default 8000
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

characters,
 approximately 2000
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

tokens),
 lower-priority slots are truncated or cleared—
identity and sensorium are never shed.
 The result is that the agent perceives a coherent,
 current view of its own state without making any tool calls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
Archivist
\series default
 runs asynchronously after each cycle as a fire-and-forget process,
 using a two-phase pipeline based on the ACE Reflector/Curator architecture 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep{ace2024}
\end_layout

\end_inset

:
 Phase
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

1 generates an honest plain-text reflection of what worked and what failed;
 Phase
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

2 takes that reflection and produces structured 
\family typewriter
NarrativeEntry
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter
CbrCase
\family default
 records via XStructor XML schema validation.
 If Phase
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

1 fails,
 a single-call fallback is used.
 If Phase
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

2 fails after Phase
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

1 succeeds,
 the reflection is preserved in logs.
 Thread assignment uses overlap scoring across location,
 domain,
 and keyword dimensions.
 CBR cases track their own utility via retrieval and outcome statistics,
 enabling self-improving retrieval over time.
 Detailed descriptions of XStructor and all other technical subsystems (canary probes,
 cross-cycle pattern detection,
 the agent-managed scheduler,
 narrative threading,
 housekeeping,
 the sandbox,
 and the web GUI) are in Appendix
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:subsystems"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Cognitive Cycle
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each cognitive cycle follows a fixed sequence:
 input reception,
 D
\begin_inset Formula $'$
\end_inset

 input gate evaluation,
 query complexity classification (routing to faster or more capable models),
 context assembly by the Curator (including sensorium injection),
 LLM inference,
 tool dispatch with per-tool safety evaluation,
 react loop until text response,
 output gate evaluation,
 response delivery,
 and asynchronous Archivist processing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
D
\begin_inset Formula $'$
\end_inset

 safety system
\series default
 (detailed in Section
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:normative"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

) evaluates at three points in this sequence.
 The 
\emph on
input gate
\emph default
 screens incoming prompts for injection attempts using canary probes and deterministic regex rules,
 with a fast-accept path that skips LLM scoring for benign operator input.
 The 
\emph on
tool gate
\emph default
 evaluates each tool call before dispatch—
this gate always runs the full LLM scorer,
 since the threat model here is a compromised agent acting on injected instructions from web content.
 The 
\emph on
output gate
\emph default
 evaluates finished responses before delivery,
 using different strategies for interactive cycles (deterministic rules only—
the operator is the quality gate) and autonomous cycles (full LLM scorer plus normative calculus).
 The name D
\begin_inset Formula $'$
\end_inset

 comes from signal detection theory:
 the system attempts to maximise discriminability between legitimate and unsafe operations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An important design decision is the 
\series bold
interactive/autonomous split
\series default
.
 Interactive input (operator typing) skips structural injection heuristics—
the operator may legitimately discuss the system's own safety mechanisms.
 Autonomous input (scheduler,
 email) uses the full evaluation stack.
\end_layout

