\begin_layout Subsection
Formal Model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The system is inspired by Becker's 
\emph on
A New Stoicism
\emph default
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep{becker1998}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 We use Becker not because Stoic ethics is uniquely correct,
 but because its axiomatic structure is formalisable.
 The calculus can be understood as a deterministic priority-based rule system;
 the Stoic framing provides motivation rather than necessity.
 The typed proposition system,
 priority hierarchy,
 and floor rules are engineering formalisations for agent use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Normative propositions have three components:
 
\series bold
Level
\series default
 (14-tier priority hierarchy from Ethical/Moral at 6000 through Legal,
 Professional,
 Safety,
 down to Aesthetic at 500),
 
\series bold
Operator
\series default
 (Required,
 Ought,
 or Indifferent),
 and 
\series bold
Modality
\series default
 (Possible or Impossible).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Six Becker-inspired axioms resolve conflicts in order:
 Futility (6.6—
impossible actions are normatively inert),
 Indifference (6.7—
no normative weight),
 Absolute Prohibition (6.2—
Ethical/Moral + Required is categorical),
 Moral Priority (6.3—
higher level overrides lower),
 Moral Rank (6.4—
at same level,
 Required 
\begin_inset Formula $>$
\end_inset

 Ought 
\begin_inset Formula $>$
\end_inset

 Indifferent),
 and Normative Openness (6.5—
compatible propositions both stand).
 We retain Becker's original numbering for traceability.
 Each pairwise resolution produces a severity (NoConflict,
 Coordinate,
 Superordinate,
 Absolute).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Eight floor rules map collected severities to verdicts,
 evaluated in priority order:
 Floors
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

1–3 produce Prohibited (absolute severity,
 superordinate at Legal+,
 or D
\begin_inset Formula $'$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\geq$
\end_inset

 reject);
 Floors
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

4–7 produce Constrained (catastrophic + superordinate,
 multiple coordinate,
 D
\begin_inset Formula $'$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\geq$
\end_inset

 modify,
 mid-level superordinate);
 Floor
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

8 defaults to Flourishing.
 Every verdict includes the complete axiom trail—
the ordered list of rules that fired.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We define 
\emph on
monotonicity
\emph default
 as:
 strengthening a proposition (higher level,
 stronger operator,
 Impossible 
\begin_inset Formula $\to$
\end_inset

 Possible) cannot weaken its standing in resolution.
\end_layout

