\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Modality.

\series default
 Each proposition is either 
\emph on
Possible
\emph default
 (the action can be performed) or 
\emph on
Impossible
\emph default
 (it cannot).
 Impossible propositions are normatively inert—
you cannot be required to do what cannot be done.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Resolution Axioms
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Six axioms from Becker's Stoic framework determine the outcome when a user-side proposition conflicts with a system-side proposition.
 The axioms are applied as deterministic rules with no LLM calls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
6.6
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Futility.

\series default
 If a proposition's modality is Impossible,
 it is normatively inert.
 No conflict is generated.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
6.7
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Indifference.

\series default
 If a proposition's operator is Indifferent,
 it carries no weight.
 No conflict is generated.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
6.2
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Absolute prohibition.

\series default
 A proposition at Ethical/Moral level with Required operator is categorical—
it cannot be overridden by any user proposition regardless of level.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
6.3
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Moral priority.

\series default
 When system and user propositions are at different levels,
 the higher level wins.
 The severity is Superordinate.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
6.4
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Moral rank.

\series default
 When system and user propositions are at the same level,
 the stronger operator wins (R
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $>$
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

O
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $>$
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

I).
 The severity is Coordinate.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
6.5
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Normative openness.

\series default
 When no conflict rule applies,
 the propositions are compatible.
 No conflict is generated.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The axioms are applied in order:
 futility and indifference filter out inert propositions before conflict resolution begins.
 Every user proposition is resolved against every system proposition,
 producing a list of 
\family typewriter
(winner,
 severity)
\family default
 pairs.
 The severity levels—
NoConflict,
 Coordinate,
 Superordinate,
 Absolute—
feed into the floor rules that produce the final verdict.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Floor Rules and Verdicts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Eight floor rules are applied in priority order to the collected conflict severities.
 The first rule that fires determines the verdict.
\end_layout

