\begin_layout Subsection
Query Complexity Classification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each user input is classified as Simple or Complex before model selection.
 Simple queries are routed to a faster,
 cheaper model (e.g.,
 claude-haiku);
 complex queries to a more capable model (e.g.,
 claude-opus).
 Classification uses a combination of heuristics (query length,
 keyword patterns) and an optional LLM classification call with a 10-second timeout.
 This provides automatic cost management without operator intervention.
\end_layout

