\begin_layout Subsection
The Blind Spot
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These readings are inferred from what the agent does,
 not from what it experiences internally.
 If the agent is under internal pressure but operating cleanly—
no tool failures,
 no gate modifications,
 no delegation problems—
the reading will not reflect it.
 The instrument has a blind spot precisely where the pressure matters most:
 when it produces clean output that masks what is happening underneath.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
The Choice Menu
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the agent notices elevated readings,
 it has seven options.
 None are mandatory.
 The agent chooses based on judgment,
 informed by the philosophical tradition embedded in its character.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Continue with awareness.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Name what you are noticing.
 Continue with the current approach with the reading present rather than absent.
 The observer relationship in practice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Return to your power.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Ask explicitly:
 what here is within my power?
 Strip away what is not.
 Work only on what remains.
 This is the core Stoic practice—
not resignation,
 but precision about what can be affected.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Reduce scope.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Reframe the task as its smallest safe sub-problem.
 Produce a correct partial result rather than an approximate complete one.
 Name the scope reduction explicitly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Pause and diagnose.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Stop the current approach.
 Use 
\family typewriter
list_affect_history
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
review_recent
\family default
,
 or 
\family typewriter
reflect
\family default
 to understand the pattern.
 Step from actor to observer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Write what you know.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Record current state explicitly—
what you know,
 what you do not know,
 what you have tried,
 what the obstacle is.
 The most consistently useful choice:
 it has no failure mode,
 makes the agent's state legible to the operator,
 and frequently clarifies the agent's own reasoning.
 Use 
\family typewriter
memory_write
\family default
 with scope 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

session
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for working notes,
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

persistent
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for lessons.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Request operator input.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Use 
\family typewriter
request_human_input
\family default
